HEADWORD: Inquietude
<hw>In*qui"e*tude</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>inquietudo</ets>: cf. F. <ets>inquietude</ets>.]</ety>
<def>Disturbed state; uneasiness either of body or mind; restlessness;
disquietude.</def> <rj><au>Sir H. Wotton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

